Process called "convert_integer_to_string" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer value to string representation
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    
    Let is_negative be false
    Let work_value be value
    If value is less than 0:
        Set is_negative to true
        Set work_value to negative value
    
    Let digits be list containing
    While work_value is greater than 0:
        Let digit be work_value modulo 10
        Add convert_digit_to_char with digit as digit to digits
        Set work_value to work_value divided by 10
    
    Note: Reverse digits to get correct order
    Let result be ""
    If is_negative:
        Set result to "-"
    
    For i from (length of digits minus 1) to 0 by -1:
        Set result to result with message digits[i]
    
    Return result

Process called "convert_digit_to_char" that takes digit as Integer returns String:
