Process called "system_call_get_character_at_index" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Runtime system call to extract character at index using runtime interface
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of text:
        Return ""
    
    Note: Use runtime interface for efficient character access
    Let char_request be dictionary containing:
        "text" as text,
        "index" as index
    
    Let char_result be system_call_string_get_char with request as char_request
    Match char_result:
        When ProcessSuccess:
            Return char_result["character"]
        When ProcessFailure:
            Return ""